class UndergroundSystem {
    constructor() {
        this.checkInInfo = {};
        this.journeyData = {};
    }

    checkIn(id, stationName, t) {
        this.checkInInfo[id] = [stationName, t];
    }

    checkOut(id, stationName, t) {
        const [startStation, startTime] = this.checkInInfo[id];
        const route = startStation + "_" + stationName;
        const duration = t - startTime;
        if (!this.journeyData.hasOwnProperty(route)) {
            this.journeyData[route] = [0, 0];
        }
        this.journeyData[route][0] += duration;
        this.journeyData[route][1] += 1;
    }

    getAverageTime(startStation, endStation) {
        const route = startStation + "_" + endStation;
        const [duration, count] = this.journeyData[route];
        return duration / count;
    }
}
```

    We use two hashmaps, one for keeping track of checkIn information and one for keeping track of journey data. When a user checks in, we store their check-in information (station and time) in the checkInInfo hashmap. When a user checks out, we retrieve their stored check-in information, calculate the duration of the journey, and store or update the journey data in the journeyData hashmap. To obtain the average time for a journey between two stations, we retrieve the aggregated journey data from the journeyData hashmap and calculate the average.

